<br>
The channels:  Market, Taxi, Rez, ooc, lfg<br>
<br>
Market has the most staying power of all the channels I think, when I logged off it was 70 people strong at around midnight pst. For sellers it is ideal, /join market, offer up your wares, then leave the channel, repeating as often as desired from wherever you happen to be. (you could even set up a macro to join/auc/leave all with one click) Buyers can sit in their zone of preference and watch the pretty spam scroll by (lag free if they dont happen to be in ecom at the time) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Taxi is self explanatory, porters can make a bit of cash and it will save those who need a lift the trouble of / all druid/wiz and spamming people with unwelcome tells.<br>
<br>
I actually didnt start Rez, and I forgot the clerics name who did (sorry) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   but he didnt promote it at all and was all alone when I found it. Theoretically, Rez works ideal in conjunction with taxi. Die anywhere on norrath? /join rez, /join taxi, a cleric will be incoming in no time (assuming you can afford the fee) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
OOC is just that, a global ooc channel because I wanted a non-vulgar name that I could promote in public channels. OOC never seemed to catch on in the couple hours I was pushing it. Everybody wanted to chat in channels with names like %#!#$%! for some reason. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
People asked what the point of an lfg chat was, and honestly I dont really know. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   The channel is probably dead now anyway, but I remember being mighty bored while lfg in seb back in the day, Im sure if all the lfg people joined they could keep themselves entertained. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
After Market started taking off I had 10 active chat channels up with around 200 total people. Spam was insane but I experienced no lag at all.<br>
<br>
I hope market catches on because I really dont like ecom, and I will probably always be in ooc, even if Im all alone, just to keep my guild officer channel a bit further away from the q key. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
edit: for those whom may not know yet, a few important chat commands:<br>
<br>
/join &lt;channel name&gt; - joins you to the named channel, or creates it if it doesnt yet exist.<br>
<br>
/list -  lists all channels you are currently in and displays number of people in each. <br>
<br>
/list &lt;channel name&gt; - lists all people in a channel (you must be in channel to use this)<br>
<br>
/&lt;channel number&gt; &lt;text&gt; - transmits text to the channel indicated.<br>
<br>
/leave &lt;channel name&gt; or /leave &lt;number&gt; - leave channel<br>
